  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic package carries a W-CON-01 weakness: the overall decision is Accepted despite several CredibilityFactor entries lacking both requiredLevel and achievedLevel, meaning the acceptance decision is not grounded in complete structured factor evidence.",
